<a id="movie-card-a" href="/movie-info?index=<%= index %>" > 
    <figure class="movie-card">
        <img src=<%= `${movie.movieCover}` %> class="movie-card-cover-img" alt="cover of the selected movie">
        <figcaption>      
            <p><span id="movie-name"><%= movie.movieName %></span></p>
            <p></strong><span id="movie-info">"<%= movie.movieInfo %> "</span></p>
            <p><strong>Genre : <span id="movie-gnere"></strong><%= movie.movieGenre %></span></p>
        </figcaption>
    </figure>
</a>

<!--
DOCUMENTATION!

This section handles passing the selected movie from the Home Page
to the Movie Info Page.

Each movie card on the homepage is generated in a loop. The loop
assigns an "index" value to every movie. That index represents the
movie’s position in the moviesData array.

FLOW OF DATA WHEN A USER CLICKS A MOVIE CARD:
1. home.ejs
   The homepage loops through the moviesData array using a for loop.
   During each iteration, it includes the movieCard.ejs partial and
   passes two values:
      - movie: the movie object
      - index: the position of that movie in the moviesData array

2. movieCard.ejs (Partial)
   The movie card is a clickable element (<a> tag).
   The index value passed from home.ejs is added to the URL as a
   query parameter:

      /movie-info?index=<%= index %>

   This creates a unique URL for each movie based on its index.

3. User Click
   When the user clicks the movie card, the browser navigates to
   /movie-info and sends the index value in the query string.

4. app.js Route
   The Express route reads the index using:

      req.query.index

   This value is used to select the correct movie from the
   moviesData array:

      moviesData[req.query.index]

5. movieInfo.ejs
   The selected movie object is passed into the template as "movie".
   The page then renders the movie’s details (name, info, genre, etc.).

SUMMARY:
home.ejs → movieCard.ejs → URL with index → app.js route → movieInfo.ejs

The index acts as a simple identifier that allows the server to
retrieve and display the correct movie from the moviesData array.
-->